                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14630373" author="esteban" created="Thu, 16 Jul 2015 21:35:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=Walom&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;Walom&quot;&gt;Roberto Arias-Yacupoma&lt;/a&gt; can you provide more details? what user is running the REST service?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14630572" author="apurtell" created="Fri, 17 Jul 2015 00:04:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s not correct, if you have the AccessController running on the cluster and ACLs set up, the REST gateway cannot bypass them, it is just another client. I think you need to provide more detail on your setup. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;User access through the gateway will have as effective principal that under which the REST gateway is running, unless you enable impersonation. Perhaps this is what you are getting at? Information on how to operate the REST gateway in a secure environment can be found in the online manual (&lt;a href=&quot;https://hbase.apache.org/book.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://hbase.apache.org/book.html&lt;/a&gt;). See especially &lt;a href=&quot;https://hbase.apache.org/book.html#security.rest.gateway&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://hbase.apache.org/book.html#security.rest.gateway&lt;/a&gt; and the previous section.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
